  <front>
   <head>HUMANE LOVE:</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">So let them love for me;</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10" />
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">My Love's as pure as their's, more unconfin'd;</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">they but love the Mind.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="2" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Can desire be ill?</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">For that which wou'd a Man with pleasure fill;</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">This more intense and active, sure must be,</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Since I both  give to thee.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="3" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="9" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">as that contains,</l>
     <l n="10" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">And more, for unto that but half pertains:</l>
     <l n="11" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Friendship one Soul to th' other doth unite,</l>
     <l n="12" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">and therefore is more bright.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="4" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="13" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Neither doth —  Religion harm,</l>
     <l n="14" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">But rather us against our Vices arm:</l>
     <l n="15" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Shall I not for a charming Mistress dye?</l>
     <l n="16" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">When Heaven commands</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
  </body>
